			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Let us summon demons, dragons, angels, and other monstrosities that actually have different abilities than our elementals.  Maybe even abilities we can control, like /pet use dragonbreath, or /pet heal %t.  They should be situational pets, but by situational I mean <span style="font-style: italic">lots of situations</span>.  (IE no Rage of Zomm crap).  Or, if the only situations they can be used are rare, make them <span style="font-style: italic">good</span> abilities and <span style="font-style: italic">good</span> situations.
<br />

<br />
While mages have traditionally been purely a damage class, I don't think a small amount of healing ability would be really out of line, if it was both unique to mages and at the cost of our pet damage.
<br />

<br />
For example, to use the healing pet you would target the tank and hit /pet heal.  The pet would move up next to the tank as if he was going to attack, but would instead start proccing heal spells.  As far as I know, no other class except maybe vaguely bard has a close range, randomized heal spell.
<br />

<br />
Or
<br />

<br />
An AA ability that lets us summon a second real pet.  HoE and that fireball thing are both good abilities, but I'd rather see a single "Dual Pet" aa ability that can be built on from there.  I'd say the second pet would have to be different from our main pets, just like HoE and Servant of Ro, but they should be commandable (and useful of course).
<br />

<br />
Ideas for secondary pets:
<br />

<br />
A pet with low dps that procced a small, short duration debuff.
<br />

<br />
A pet that would cast small heal spells on the main pet.
<br />

<br />
A pet that would cast short duration buffs on the main pet.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
