			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would much rather be able to create a golem than summon random specific use pets.  The 4 elemental pets are good enough for mages, and I can't see a use for any other pets that wouldn't be over powering or infringe on another class.  
<br />

<br />
I really would like the option to use tradeskills to create golems.  Make them expensive, take some xp from you, and need high trade skills to create but i think it'd be sweet.  
<br />

<br />
Here's how it'd work in my mind.  You create the base golem, when you do this you get an item that has unlimited charges (or gives you a hotkey like AA do) that summons a lvl 1 golem.  This creation would be very expensive and requiree a high research skill along with JC, pottery, and smithing.  JC used to create the item that binds the golem to your control, pottery to create the general form of the golem, smithing to create the armor and weapons of the golem, and finally research to animate the golem.  
<br />

<br />
Once this golem is created you could create items that would make it grow in power and also give it a purpose.  The purposes would be:
<br />
Melee
<br />
Shielding
<br />
Utility
<br />

<br />
Melee is pretty self explanitory, the golem gets stronger and goes around and hits things, not nearly as good as a player cast pets but it does some dmg.  
<br />

<br />
Shielding, basically it does its best to taunt mobs off of its caster and also /shields them continually.  This golem would have no offensive abilities.  If possible it would be neat to have two types of golems, one for magical attacks and one for physical.
<br />

<br />
Utility, I'd like to see somethign that could carry items for you.  like you hand them a bag and it hands you a token back.  When you give it the token you get the bag back.  I don't think something like that is feasible but I would like to see it allow you to carry more, or remove encumberances all together (like the horse but usable anywhere)
<br />

<br />
The items that would determine the purpose of the golem, along with the strenght, would also be tradeskill related but would ultimately require some form of research skill.
<br />
Yeah the idea are far fetched, but after starting on the "Recharging the Portals" quest I've really wanted to create/have a goelm with me even if he is weak.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
